description:
Python's dictionaries are stunningly good. Over the years, many great
ideas have combined together to produce the modern implementation in
Python 3.6.

This fun talk uses pictures and little bits of pure python code to
explain all of the key ideas and how they evolved over time.

Includes newer features such as key-sharing, compaction, and versioning.
title: Modern Python Dictionaries -- A confluence of a dozen great ideas
